  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ShannonsController
    This class is an interface that defines the methods available to the controller.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ShannonsGraphicPanel
    This class represents a view in the MVC design pattern.
    ShannonsModel
    This class holds the data for a simulation of Shannon's Theorem and is the model in the MVC design pattern, inherits from Observable.
    ShannonsPanel
    This class represents a view in the MVC design pattern.
    ShannonsSliderPanel
    This class represents a view in the MVC design pattern.
    ShannonsTheorem
    This class implements ShannonsController and uses a delegate design pattern by delegating most of its functionality to the ShannonsModel class.
    ShannonsTheoremLauncher
    This class creates the MVC objects, assembles them together, and then runs the program in a JFrame.
